  <h1>Brighter Beginnings Adopt a Family Shopping Tips</h>

    <h2>GIFTS (the client profile provides you with specific needs of the family)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Please provide at least one fun and one practical gift for each family member.</p></li>
      <li><p>Wrap and tag each gift.</p></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FOOD (optional)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><p>If desired, provide for a nice holiday meal (or more) by purchasing grocery gift certificates available at all major grocery stores.</p></li>
      <li><p>We welcome canned food and other non-perishables if boxed securely with no box weighing over 30 lbs.</p></li> 
    </ul>

    <h2>PACKAGING</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Place all items in sturdy boxes with lids and tape securely to close</p></li> 
      <li><p>Maximum weight for boxes is 30 lbs.</p></li> 
      <li><p>Boldly write the Family Code Number (found on the Family Profile) on all 4 sides and the top of each box.</p></li> 
    </ul>

    <h2>DELIVERY LOCATION AND DROP OFF DATES – directions are on the website</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Gifts must be dropped off at the location associated with the family (i.e. Richmond family, Richmond drop off).</p></li> 
      <li><p>Please bring your adopted family profile form and the in-kind donor receipt form (found on the web site), filled out, to the drop-off site.</p></li> 
    </ul>

    <p>*Please note that only new items are accepted at this time of the year (November/December) for your “adopted” family.</p>
